Seq clean-up: - Centrifuge at 1650rcf for 2 minutes- Add 65µL of Ethanol and Sodium       acetate mix to each well-Replace PCR mat and invert plate to shake down twice by turning plate upside down to ensure thorough mixing.-turn plate upright and tap firmly, stand at room temperature for a minute then centrifuge plate at 3220rcf for 15minutes.- after spin, remove the ethanol sodium acetate mix with a firm flick.-Place inverted plate into centrifuge at 1650rcf for 2minutes to remove any residual ethanol sodium acetate mix.-Add 150µL of 70% Ethanol to each well and allow to stand at room temperature for 1 minute.-Flick out the ethanol and spin plate at 1650rcf for 2minutes to remove any residual ethanol.-Allow plate to stand at room temperature to air dry.-Resuspend pellet  with 10µL 50/50 Hi-Di/RNase DNase free distilled water solution.-Run PCR as below:Denature: 95°C for 2 minutesHold: 15°C for 8
CE instrument: ABI 3130XL sequencer 
Injection buffer: 50/50 Hi-Di/RNase DNase free distilled
Capillary length: 50cm
Capillary polymer: POP-7™ Polymer for 3730/3730xl DNA Analyzers
